{
  "stem": "1857.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was one man in our group, in our barrack, [INAUDIBLE], in our sleeping quarters, who was a tremendously optimistic person.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Besides that, he worked in Schindler's office.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, from time to time, he heard news on the radio.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But besides hearing the news, he wanted to keep us alive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he used to come every evening and tell us all kind of the stories about victories of the Allies, how the Germans are on the run, and how the Russians are getting close.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And like a hundred people used to surround him and listen to his stories.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he had some-- some were factual, and some were just improvised in order to-- to keep our spirits up.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But as the war was coming to an end, he listened to the radio, and he knew already that the Germans are in Prague, and that they're going ahead.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were in eastern part of Czechoslovakia, in Sudetenland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we know that the end is coming.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] As I told you, at one point, news came that the Russian POWs were digging ditches.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Czech underground, which was always in touch with us, informed us that the Russian POWs are digging ditches for us-- that Leopold, the commandant of the camp, wants to kill everybody in the camp.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Schindler found out about it, and he went to Berlin.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "How he did it, I don't know, but he-- a letter was sent from Leopold's unit that he should go right away to Prague and report to an SS unit in Prague.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And actually, he was sent to Prague when Prague was already surrounded by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was all Schindler's doing, that he got rid of him.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
